Top Cat, known in Spanish as Don Gato y su pandilla, or simply Don Gato, is an animated TV series only 30 episodes, designed and produced by Hanna-Barbera in 1961 and aired in prime time on ABC from the United States from September 27, 1961 until April 8, 1962.
The protagonist, Don Gato, is the leader of a gang of feral cats in Manhattan: Panza (Fancy-Fancy) Espanto (Spook), Benito B. Bodoque (Benny the Ball), Demosthenes (The Brain) and Cucho (Choo-Choo). Meanwhile, Officer Carlos Matute (Officer Dibble) neighborhood police unsuccessfully tries to catch them and take them to jail. One reason for the arrest was that Don Gato was to use a phone as his own but that was owned by the police.
